lead_paragraph: Rachael Grinham of Australia came from match point down to take the women’s title from Nicol David, ranked No. 1 in the world, in Manchester, England. Grinham outlasted David, the world champion from Malaysia, 7-9 4-9 9-3 10-8 9-1, to regain the title and defeat David for the first time in 16 attempts.
